                            <comment id="12830678" author="jdcryans" created="Sun, 7 Feb 2010 07:19:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that adds the proper exception handling, made against branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12831566" author="stack" created="Tue, 9 Feb 2010 18:03:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you test killing the server hosting .META. during an upload? The relocation of .META. does seem gratuitous.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should comment be about regions and not tables?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+          &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Only relocate the parent table &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; necessary&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12831872" author="stack" created="Wed, 10 Feb 2010 05:14:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried shutting down the server hosting .META. in a cluster with this patch in place.  I get connection refused.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
100 row(s) in 2.1810 seconds
hbase(main):002:0&amp;gt; scan &apos;TestTable&apos;, {LIMIT =&amp;gt; 100}
NativeException: java.net.ConnectException: Connection refused

hbase(main):003:0&amp;gt; scan &apos;TestTable&apos;, {LIMIT =&amp;gt; 100}
NativeException: java.net.ConnectException: Connection refused

hbase(main):004:0&amp;gt; scan &apos;TestTable&apos;, {LIMIT =&amp;gt; 100}
NativeException: java.net.ConnectException: Connection refused

hbase(main):005:0&amp;gt; scan &apos;TestTable&apos;, {LIMIT =&amp;gt; 100}
NativeException: java.net.ConnectException: Connection refused
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Without it, shell works fine as .META. moves servers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12832108" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 10 Feb 2010 18:23:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems I forgot to handle an exception, let&apos;s fix that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12832138" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 10 Feb 2010 19:22:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I forgot to check for ConnectionError, so I think the best is to do the reverse of what the other patch did e.g. relocate only if we don&apos;t get RegionOfflineException or NoServerForRegionException.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12832189" author="stack" created="Wed, 10 Feb 2010 20:43:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch.  I tried various combinations of shutdown of servers carrying root and meta and client kept-on keeping-on.  I&apos;d say go commit it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12832272" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 10 Feb 2010 23:03:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to branch and trunk. Thanks for trying it out Stack.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
